General Privacy Policy
TouchRetouch Privacy Policy
Batched Privacy Policy
1. WHO SHOULD READ THIS PRIVACY POLICY
When you access and interact with our Website and iOS mobile App and use our services, we collect and process your personal data.
This Privacy Policy contains important information about how and why we collect and use your data when you access and interact with our website, mobile apps, and services.
2. WHO WE ARE
Registered business name: ADVA Soft GmbH
Business address: Scherenbergstraße 8, 10439 Berlin, Germany
Business email: support@adva-soft.com
3. HOW TO CONTACT US
For any matter or questions relating to the processing of your personal data, you can contact us either via post or by email at:
Business address: Scherenbergstraße 8, 10439 Berlin, Germany
Business email: support@adva-soft.com
4. HOW WE COLLECT YOUR PERSONAL DATA
Data you voluntarily provide to us
You voluntarily provide us with your personal data when you do the following:
When you enter your financial data such as your card details and your billing address to make a purchase.
When you provide your basic personal information such as your email address to fill out customer surveys on our website and within the app.
Data we automatically collect about you
In addition to personal data you directly disclose to us, we also use various third-party tools to automatically collect personal data about you:
When you visit our website, we place cookies on your device to collect personal data about you. Visit our Cookies Policy to learn about how we use cookies.
When you download and use our mobile app, we automatically collect information about how you interact with it via the following third-party tools:
https://firebase.google.com/docs/analytics
When you download and use our mobile app, we automatically collect information about how you interact with it via the following third-party tools:
https://mixpanel.com/legal/app-store-privacy-details/
When you make purchases within the app, we collect data about your purchases and your purchase tendencies and use this data for analytics purposes by using the following tool:
https://www.revenuecat.com/
We use
Appsflyer Service
to process your personal data such as:
“Technical Information”:
This covers technical information concerning an End User’s mobile device or computer,
                                  such as browser type, device type, and model, CPU, system language, memory, OS version, Wi-Fi status, time stamp and zone,
                                  device motion parameters and carrier.
“Technical Identifiers”:
TThis refers to various unique identifiers that generally only identify a computer,
                                  device, browser or Application such as IP address.
"Engagement Information":
This includes information relating to our campaigns and End User actions, such as clicks on our ads, and ad impressions viewed.
To ensure that your personal data is processed as per our instructions, we enter into a Data Processing Agreement with AppsFlyer, which can be found here:
https://www.appsflyer.com/gdpr/dpa.pdf
For more information about how Appsflyer processes personal data, visit their Services Privacy Policy here:
https://www.appsflyer.com/legal/services-privacy-policy/
Unsplash Integration
When you use our Unsplash integration feature, we collect and share data with Unsplash to enable the functionality of selecting and using backgrounds from Unsplash within our app. This integration requires us to adhere to Unsplash's API Terms and Privacy Policy.
For more information about how Unsplash processes personal data, visit their Policy here:
https://unsplash.com/privacy
TouchRetouch is not responsible for the content selected and used by users from Unsplash. Users bear full responsibility for ensuring that their use of Unsplash images is appropriate and lawful.
5. WHAT PERSONAL DATA DO WE COLLECT ABOUT YOU
Through the methods described in Section 4, we may collect the following categories of personal data about you:
Basic personal details such as your name and email address,
Financial data such as your bank details, card information, and billing address,
Information about your devices such as device&hardware model, device identifier, and IP address,
Data related to how you access, use and interact with our website, mobile app, and services. For instance, we collect data about actions you take within our apps such as making a purchase or clicks.
Data related to individual purchases you make and your purchase habits and tendencies
Data about the specific actions you take on the photos you edit via our app such as the removal of certain objects inside the photos you upload and the place and the type of object you remove
Information about your activity across other apps and websites such as your engagement with our ads on third-party apps and websites, your clicks, your activities
In addition, we may collect data related to your use of our mobile app such as:
Number of sessions
Session duration
Operating systems
Device model
Geography
App opens
App updates
In-app purchases
6. HOW WE USE YOUR PERSONAL DATA
We only process your personal data for specific purposes such as:
To enable you to access and use our services and features;
To contact you to provide information and updates about our App;
To carry out research and analytics about how you use and interact with the App/Sites;
To improve our app, website, and services by collecting data about your usage of our services;
To resolve disputes in relation to the relationship between you and us;
To investigate fraud, to protect and enforce our legal rights;
To send you promotional materials about our services;
To deliver a series of advertisement products such as real time bidding from third party advertisers(Website data).
To analyze the type, place, and form of objects you remove from the photos you upload so that we can better understand which objects our users want to remove more frequently. This will help us fine-tune our algorithm so that we can offer our users better auto-selection and object removal functionality.
Sharing data with advertisers and ad-performance measurement:: To share your data with third-party advertşsers so that they can measure the effectiveness of their ad campaigns on our app.
Personalized apps: To track your activity across our app and also on third-party apps and websites so that we can deliver personalized ads to you on our app, tailored to your specific interests and needs.
Ad retargeting: To retarget you with ads on other apps and websites.
