9. YOUR RIGHTS IN RELATION TO YOUR DATA
You can exercise some or all of the following rights depending on the law that applies to the processing of your personal data.
Right of Access:
You can make a request to find out if we process your data and obtain copies of personal data we hold about You subject to limitations described in applicable laws.
Right to Rectification:
You may ask Us to correct any inaccuracies or false information related to your personal data.
Right to Erasure of Your Data:
Subject to the limitation set forth in applicable laws, you can submit a request for deletion of your data.
Right to Restriction of Processing:
You may request the restriction of processing of your data on the ground that the data is not accurate or the processing activity is not legitimate.
Right to Object:
You may raise objections to processing of your data if we are relying on legitimate interests.
Right to Data Portability:
If applicable, you can ask for transfer of all personal data we hold about You to another organisation.
How to exercise these rights
To exercise any of your rights, please contact us at support@adva-soft.com. We may need to verify your identity before processing your request to ensure the security of your personal data. We will respond to your request within one month of receiving it. This period may be extended by two further months where necessary, considering the complexity and number of the requests.
10. HOW TO EXERCISE YOUR LEGAL RIGHTS
If you decide to exercise your rights we listed in Section 9, you should get in touch with Us by one of the following ways to submit your request:
Application by post: Scherenbergstraße 8, 10439 Berlin, Germany
Application by email: support@adva-soft.com
When you submit your request by one of these methods, you should include the following information within your request:
Provide us with your name & surname & contact details or other data that may help us to determine if we process Your data.
We reserve the right to ask for any additional information to verify your identity and authenticity of your request.
We aim to respond to your request within the time limits imposed by relevant laws.
11. NOTICE ABOUT FACEBOOK PIXEL
We use Facebook Pixel on our Website, which is a piece of code that enables us to track our users’ activity on our Website.
Via Facebook Pixel, we collect the following types of personal data about you when you visit our website:
The HTTP header information containing particulars such as user agent, country of residence, and language preferences of the web browser or app used (Details such as user agent, country of residence, language preferences);
Information about events such as “Page view”, clicks;
Online identifiers, such as IP addresses and Facebook-related identifiers, or device identifiers.
12. NOTICE ABOUT PAYMENT METHODS AND PAYMENT DATA
Notice about Apple Pay
When you make a purchase via Apple Pay to access and use our services, Apple collects and uses your personal data.
To learn more about what types of personal data Apple collects and how your data is used, please refer to Apple Privacy Policy:
https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/
https://www.apple.com/uk/legal/privacy/data/en/apple-pay/
Notice about Paypal
When you make a payment via Paypal, Paypal collects and processes your personal data.
To learn more about what types of personal data Paypal collects and how your data is used, please refer to  Paypal privacy notice:
https://www.paypal.com/us/legalhub/privacy-full
Notice about Google Pay and other methods
When you make a payment via Google Pay, Google play Gift Cards and Promo Codes, Google collects and processes your personal data.
To learn more about what types of personal data Google collects and how your data is used, please refer to  Google Payments Privacy Notice:
https://payments.google.com/payments/apis-secure/get_legal_document?ldo=0&ldt=privacynotice&ldl=en
https://support.google.com/googlepay/answer/7643925?sjid=7011834154728981607-EU&visit_id=638211240334863876-3733807392&rd=1
13. TRANSFER OF YOUR DATA OUT OF THE EU AND THE UK
When we transfer your data from the European Economic Area (“EEA”) or UK to countries that the
                                European Commission has not deemed to provide an adequate level of protection, we normally do so on the basis of
                                Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission for such purpose.
                                You may request a copy of the Standard Contractual Clauses by contacting us as described below.
14. HOW TO DELETE YOUR PERSONAL DATA AND REVOKE PERMISSIONS
When you delete the App from your device, all your data, including your imported photos will be deleted within the App.
We do not store your photos on our servers.
If you have given Us access to your photos, but wish to turn this off, you can do so by the following methods:
From RETOUCH app — Settings, Privacy Details, ALLOW RETOUCH TO ACCESS, Photos, None;
From default Settings app — RETOUCH, ALLOW RETOUCH TO ACCESS, Photos, None.
15. HOW TO TURN OFF SHARING OF YOUR DATA FOR ANALYTICS PURPOSES
You can turn off the sharing of your data related to your usage of the app for analytics purposes directly within the app:
To turn off data sharing, go to Settings > Share App Usage Analytics and toggle off the data sharing.
16. HOW TO FILE A COMPLAINT WITH SUPERVISORY AUTHORITIES
For EU & UK users:
If you are located in the EU or the UK, you can file a complaint with the competent Data Protection Authority within that country.
For example, if you reside in the UK, you can contact the ICO via the following ways:
The ICO’s address:
Information Commissioner’s Office
Wycliffe House
Water Lane
Wilmslow
Cheshire
SK9 5AF
Helpline number: 0303 123 1113
ICO website:
https://www.ico.org.uk
For country specific complaint processes, you may refer to the following directory to contact the relevant supervisory authority:
https://iapp.org/resources/global-privacy-directory/
17. CHANGES TO PRIVACY POLICY
We reserve the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy as we deem appropriate.
You should regularly check our Privacy Policy page to see new changes.
